videos.description: UCLA's Josh Rosen gets sacked for the second time in the first quarter. this time by Huskies' Vita Vea.
videos.headline: Rosen sacked for the second time in 1st

videos.description: Huskies QB Jake Browning finds his way to the end zone by pushing through the defense up the middle.
videos.headline: Washington gets first TD of game

videos.description: Bruins' Josh Rosen finds Jordan Wilson for a UCLA touchdown, and later misses the field goal. Bruins trail 10-9.
videos.headline: UCLA quickly gets TD in 2nd quarter

videos.description: Washington's Salvon Ahmed with an 82-yard kick off return, putting the Bruins in the red zone.
videos.headline: Huskies' Ahmed returns ball for 82 yards

videos.description: Huskies Lavon Coleman pushes through the pile for another Washington touchdown.
videos.headline: Washington quickly respond with TD

videos.description: Washington's Myles Gaskin is handed off the ball and makes a great run along the sidelines for 37 yards.
videos.headline: Huskies' Gaskin with great run

videos.description: Washington's head coach discusses their running game and how their defense is able to hold UCLA at 9 points.
videos.headline: Coach Petersen discusses Huskies' run game

videos.description: Bruins quarterback Josh Rosen heads to the locker room in the third quarter with apparent hand injury.
videos.headline: UCLA QB Rosen leaves the game in the 3rd

videos.description: Washington's Lavon Coleman runs in a 33-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Coleman extends Huskies' lead with TD

videos.description: Another big run by Salvon Ahmed for 34 yards, avoiding multiple tackles. and puts the Huskies in scoring position.
videos.headline: Big run by Washington's Ahmed

videos.description: Washington's Jake Browning first pass in the third quarter is intercepted by UCLA's Darnay Holmes.
videos.headline: Huskies' QB's first pass in the 3rd is intercepted

videos.description: Huskies go with a wildcat formation, and the ball is snapped to Myles Gaskin who runs the ball up the middle for a touchdown.
videos.headline: Washington's' Gaskin with TD

videos.description: Bruins' backup QB Devon Modster finds Darren Andrews by the left pylon for a touchdown.
videos.headline: UCLA gets a 4-yard TD

videos.description: Lavon Coleman gets the hand off and runs across the field towards the left pylon for a Huskies touchdown.
videos.headline: Coleman with 3rd TD for Washington

videos.description: Washington's Kamari Pleasant is hit and fumbles the ball. UCLA's Osa Odighizuwa picks it up and avoids multiple tacklers for a 50-yard touchdown.
videos.headline: Huskies fumble leads to UCLA TD

videos.description: Washington's head coach Chris Petersen talks  about his offense in a 44-23 win over UCLA and the performance of his backfield.
videos.headline: Petersen discusses Washington's offensive performance

videos.description: Josh Rosen leaves in the second half with what appears to be an injured finger and doesn't return to the game, Jake Browning throws for just 98 yards in Washington's 44-23 win.
videos.headline: UCLA falls to Washington

videos.description: Washington's Vita Vea breaks down the Huskies' game plan going into today's game and putting the loss against Arizona State behind them.
videos.headline: Huskies' Vita discusses defense's game plan
